honeywell.printer.configuration.dpl

Class AutoUpdate_DPL

  • java.lang.Object
    • honeywell.printer.configuration.dpl.PrinterData_DPL
      • honeywell.printer.configuration.dpl.PrinterState_DPL
        • honeywell.printer.configuration.dpl.AutoUpdate_DPL
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class AutoUpdate_DPL
extends PrinterState_DPL
    This class handles the Auto Update data from the [STX] KcQQQ query as well as accessors to read the data values.

    This class supports the following possible parameters:

    ParameterDescription
    1Wireless Update Upgrade Type
    2Configuration File Name
    3TFTP Server IP Address
    5Upgrade Package Version
    6Beeper Enable
    7Security Credential File Format
    8Status Message Print Mode
    10FTP User Name
    11FTP Password(WRITE-ONLY)
    12FTP Server Name or Address
    13FTP Server Port
    14Print Message Stored Label for Auto Update Proces
    15Print Message Mode after Auto Update Process
    16Displayed Menu Name after Auto Update Process
    17Menu Name Display Mode after Auto Update Process
    18FTP Feedback Template File
    19FTP Feedback File Enable
    20FTP Feedback File Subdirectory
    21Print Server IP Address
    22Print Server Name
    23Print Server Port
    24Print Server Connection Mode
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

    • Constructor Detail

      • AutoUpdate_DPL

        public AutoUpdate_DPL(ConnectionBase conn)
        The default constructor will initialize the class with default values.

        Initially all of the _IsValid parameters will be false because no data has been processed. To 'populate' the values, the object must invoke @see PrinterState_DPL.queryPrinter(int) with the query response string.

        Parameters:
        conn - connection to printer
